Adjust rack to top position (middle and top positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. (TIP: For a smoother texture, peel potatoes first.) Strip thyme leaves from stems until you have @thyme{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4); mince leaves. Reserve remaining thyme sprigs for the next step. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and sliced, whites separated from greens); mince whites. Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(halved and thinly sliced). Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}(minced).

Place potatoes and reserved thyme sprigs in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil; cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot; remove and discard thyme sprigs. Mash with @sour cream{4%tablespoon} and @butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) using a #potato masher{} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While potatoes cook, in a #medium bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%ounce}, @panko breadcrumbs{¼%cup}, scallion whites, half the @fry seasoning{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest later), @water{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), @salt{¾%tsp} (1½ tsp for 4), and a pinch of pepper.

Form into 10-12 (20-24 for 4) 1 1/2-inch meatballs.

Place meatballs on one side of a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} using @cooking oil{1%tablespoon}. Toss green beans on empty side with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.

Roast on top rack until meatballs are cooked through and green beans are browned and tender, ~{14-16%minutes}. (For 4 servings, divide between 2 sheets; roast meatballs on middle rack and green beans on top rack.)

Meanwhile, melt @butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{7-9%minutes}. Stir in garlic and minced thyme; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add a drizzle of oil, @flour{1%tablespoon}, and remaining Fry Seasoning; cook, stirring, until lightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Whisk in @water{¾%cup} (1 1/2 cups for 4) and @beef stock concentrate{1}. Bring to a simmer, whisking, until thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low; stir in another @butter{1%TBSP} until melted.

Season gravy with salt and pepper. Add meatballs and stir to coat. (TIP: If gravy seems too thick, stir in a splash of water.) Turn off heat.

Divide mashed potatoes between plates; top with meatballs and gravy. Add green beans to the side. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.